---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Allianz', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Bupa', href: '/compare/bupa-global-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Network Size', cigna: '1.5M+ providers', bupa: '1.2M+ providers', allianz: '850K+ providers' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Claims Speed', cigna: '5-10 days', bupa: '5-7 days', allianz: '10-15 days' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', cigna: 'Standard', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Enhanced' },
  { feature: 'Customer Service', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Mobile App', cigna: 'Best in class', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Basic' },
  { feature: 'No-Claims Discount', cigna: 'No', bupa: 'Yes (up to 50%)', allianz: 'No' },
  { feature: 'Lifetime Renewal', cigna: 'Yes', bupa: 'Yes', allianz: 'Yes' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', cigna: '$180-240/mo', bupa: '$200-280/mo', allianz: '$150-200/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 50', cigna: '$300-380/mo', bupa: '$340-420/mo', allianz: '$260-340/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 40', cigna: '$350-450/mo', bupa: '$400-500/mo', allianz: '$300-400/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', cigna: '$500-650/mo', bupa: '$550-700/mo', allianz: '$420-550/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Best Premium Expat Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare the top 3 international health insurers: Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and Allianz Care. Coverage, pricing, networks, and which is best for your situation."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Which Premium Plan Is Right for You?"
  subheadline="The three most popular comprehensive expat health insurers compared. Here's what actually matters."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Overall</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Largest network, best app, most convenient. Pay more for a smoother experience.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Premium service, no-claims discounts, fastest claims. Higher starting price.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">10-20% cheaper, best mental health coverage. Smaller network, slower claims.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    All three are excellent choices backed by major global insurers. You won't go wrong with any of them. The differences come down to your priorities: convenience, service quality, or value.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Largest Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">US Expertise</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the go-to choice for expats who want the smoothest possible healthcare experience. Their network of 1.5M+ providers means you'll almost always find a direct billing option nearby. Walk in, show your card, walk out without paying.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Industry-leading mobile app and online portal</li>
    <li>Largest global provider network</li>
    <li>Excellent direct billing arrangements</li>
    <li>Strong US coverage for American expats</li>
    <li>Responsive 24/7 customer service</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Higher premiums than Allianz (10-15%)</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage has session limits</li>
    <li>No loyalty discounts for healthy members</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats who value convenience over cost savings. Families. Americans abroad. Anyone who hates paperwork.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No-Claims Discount</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Fast Claims</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global is the premium choice for expats who want white-glove service. Their claims processing is the fastest in the industry, and they're the only major insurer offering no-claims discounts up to 50%—which can offset their higher starting prices over time.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Fastest claims processing (5-7 days)</li>
    <li>No-claims discount up to 50%</li>
    <li>Premium customer service experience</li>
    <li>Strong in Europe and Asia</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Highest starting premiums of the three</li>
    <li>App and digital experience not as polished as Cigna</li>
    <li>No-claims discount requires staying healthy</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Healthy expats who rarely claim (maximize no-claims discount). Retirees wanting premium service. Those planning long-term coverage.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Europe Expert</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care is the smart choice for budget-conscious expats who still want comprehensive coverage. Their premiums run 10-20% below Cigna and Bupa, and they offer the best mental health coverage of the three—important for expats dealing with the stresses of life abroad.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>10-20% lower premiums than competitors</li>
    <li>Enhanced mental health coverage included</li>
    <li>Flexible, customizable plans</li>
    <li>Strong European network and expertise</li>
    <li>German efficiency and reliability</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Smaller network (850K vs 1.5M providers)</li>
    <li>Claims processing slower (10-15 days)</li>
    <li>Mobile app less polished</li>
    <li>More reimbursement vs direct billing</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious expats. Anyone needing mental health support. Europeans. Those comfortable with reimbursement claims.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Cigna, Bupa, and Allianz based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Pricing varies based on age, location, deductible, and coverage level. Here's a general comparison for comprehensive plans excluding US coverage:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive plans, worldwide excluding US, with moderate deductibles. Actual quotes vary by individual factors.
  </p>

  <h3>The Real Cost Calculation</h3>

  <p>
    Don't just compare premium prices. Consider the total cost:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bupa's no-claims discount:</strong> If you rarely claim, Bupa's 50% discount makes them competitive or even cheaper over 5+ years</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz's value:</strong> 15% lower premiums = $500-1,500/year savings for most profiles</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna's convenience:</strong> Less time dealing with claims = less stress and time wasted</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want the largest network and easiest direct billing</li>
        <li>Value a great mobile app and digital experience</li>
        <li>Are American or need strong US healthcare ties</li>
        <li>Have a family and want streamlined coverage</li>
        <li>Hate dealing with reimbursement claims</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are generally healthy and rarely claim</li>
        <li>Want to earn no-claims discounts over time</li>
        <li>Value premium, white-glove service</li>
        <li>Plan to keep coverage for many years</li>
        <li>Live in Europe or Asia</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want comprehensive coverage at a lower price</li>
        <li>Need strong mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Live in Europe or are European</li>
        <li>Don't mind handling some reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Move between countries frequently</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Which of these three is cheapest?</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care is typically 10-20% cheaper than Cigna and Bupa for comparable coverage. However, Bupa's no-claims discount (up to 50%) can make them competitive or cheaper over 5+ years if you rarely use your insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Which has the best network?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global has the largest network at 1.5M+ providers, followed by Bupa (1.2M+) and Allianz (850K+). In major cities, all three have excellent coverage. The difference matters more in smaller cities or rural areas.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I switch between these providers later?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, you can switch at any renewal period. However, any conditions that developed while covered become pre-existing for the new insurer. If you develop health issues, switching becomes more complicated.
  </p>

  <h3>Which is best for mental health coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers the most generous mental health benefits with higher session limits and better coverage for ongoing treatment. Cigna and Bupa cover mental health but with more restrictions.
  </p>

  <h3>Do any of these cover the US?</h3>
  <p>
    All three offer US coverage as an add-on, which increases premiums by 30-50%. For frequent US visitors or Americans abroad, Cigna has the strongest US network and understanding of American healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
